oakcurric:unit-2728
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Urban Life: Drawing and design"@en ;
  curric:slug "urban-life-drawing-and-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will learn the art of portraiture in greater depth. They will
  learn how artists create expressions, mood and feeling in their portraits using facial
  features, colour, lighting and props."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils previous observational and imaginative
  investigations of urban and natural environments. It provides opportunities to conceptualise,
  imagine and invent, and introduces them to design thinking.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2728-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2728-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2728-3 ;
  curric:id "2728"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.627391Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw .

oakcurric:unit-2726
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Street Art: digital and new media"@en ;
  curric:slug "street-art-digital-and-new-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will study street art in contemporary culture. They will consider graffiti
  in the context of lettering artforms and graphic design. They will learn how to draw
  graffiti letters and street art graphics before designing their own street art composition
  for a community space artwork."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit explores art in a community setting and encourages pupils to
  think about personal expression in public spaces. They revisit concepts of typography,
  lettering, and composition to deepen their understanding and application of graphic design
  concepts and processes in new contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2726-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2726-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2726-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2726-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2726-5 ;
  curric:id "2726"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.033483Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-2722
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Photography and painting: facial expressions in portraiture"@en ;
  curric:slug "photography-and-painting-facial-expressions-in-portraiture" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will learn the art of portraiture in greater depth. They will
  learn how artists create expressions, mood and feeling in their portraits using facial
  features, colour, lighting and props."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on earlier explorations of portraiture. Pupils use
  observational skills and their knowledge of light and tone to create work with expressive
  purpose. They are able to take and use photographs as source material which they use in this
  unit for their own investigations.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2722-6 ;
  curric:id "2722"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.161399Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-2727
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "New Pop Art: sculpture and mixed-media"@en ;
  curric:slug "new-pop-art-sculpture-and-mixed-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this conceptual art unit, pupils will make art in a medium of their choice on a
  topical contemporary theme. They will investigate how and why Pop artists from the 1960s
  to the present day created art."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In previous units pupils drew on contemporary cultural references and
  developed and were introduced to graphic design contexts. In this unit they explore concepts
  of culture generating and culture making, applying knowledge from the previous unit. They
  will develop many of the independent art skills of researching, thinking and idea development
  needed in key stage 3. Teachers will act as facilitators rather than instructors to enable
  pupils to realise their own, independent ideas, rather than prescribing or dictating
  outcomes.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2727-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2727-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2727-3 ;
  curric:id "2727"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.332430Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2729
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Meaning and symbolism in art: drawing and painting"@en ;
  curric:slug "meaning-and-symbolism-in-art-drawing-and-painting" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will investigate how artists create meaning and tell stories through their
  art. They will investigate symbolism in art and develop understanding that visual art,
  craft and design has multiple meanings beyond its surface depiction to support the
  development of their own visual literacy."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils apply critical and contextual skills to analyse the
  narratives and codes within artworks from different times and cultures. They develop their
  visual literacy and ability to use codes, symbols and visual metaphors in their own art work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2729-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2729-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2729-3 ;
  curric:id "2729"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.347729Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage .

oakcurric:unit-3841
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Art for change: visual voices"@en ;
  curric:slug "art-for-change-visual-voices" ;
  rdfs:comment """Made in collaboration with October Gallery. the unit explores how artists use
  visual storytelling to express ideas about people and change. Pupils create symbolic work,
  experiment with shadow and silhouettes, and design placards that use colour, shape, words,
  and symbols to share messages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will be ready to build on their knowledge by connecting memory,
  history, protest, and personal expression through more advanced techniques. Pupils can move
  beyond simply making art to considering how images carry meaning. This unit introduces more
  complex processes (carbon transfer, silhouette work, screen printing), which stretch their
  creative skills and prepare them for Key Stage 3.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3841-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3841-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3841-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3841-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3841-5 ;
  curric:id "3841"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.487542Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 .

oakcurric:unit-3834
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Charting self: exploring portrait and identity"@en ;
  curric:slug "charting-self-exploring-portrait-and-identity" ;
  rdfs:comment """Made in collaboration with October Gallery, in this unit pupils express personal
  identity through portraiture, material, memory and imagination. Pupils create textured
  paintings, symbolic surfaces, close-up feature portraits, and expressive self-maps that
  combine journey and face."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This Year 6 unit supports pupils as they reflect on identity before
  transitioning to secondary school. Linking emotion with creativity, it explores how culture,
  history, and place shape us. Pupils build confidence through artist study, expressive making,
  and personal exploration.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3834-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3834-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3834-3 ;
  curric:id "3834"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.548744Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 .

oakcurric:unit-2707
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The Rainforest: drawing and painting"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-rainforest-drawing-and-painting" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will learn about different artists who used forest scapes as their subject.
  They will create rubbings and make a collage from objects they have collected, before
  making observational drawings and developing and realising their own rainforest painting."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit incorporates more advanced colour mixing and use of tone and
  hue, as well as proportion and perspective to create depth and atmosphere.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2707-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2707-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2707-3 ;
  curric:id "2707"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.794287Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-3835
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Clothes and culture: wearable art"@en ;
  curric:slug "clothes-and-culture-wearable-art" ;
  rdfs:comment """Made in collaboration with October Gallery this unit brings together diverse
  visual languages from across time and place, encouraging children to see wearable art not
  simply as adornment, but as a powerful form of communication, one that celebrates
  identity, and gives voice to stories that matter."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit explores how clothing, sculpture, and pattern can express
  identity, memory, and resistance. Pupils investigate the body as both subject and structure,
  using wrapping, dressing, sculpting, and printing to tell visual stories rooted in personal
  and collective experience.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3835-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3835-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3835-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3835-4 ;
  curric:id "3835"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.388799Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 .

oakcurric:unit-2718
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Recording, noticing, and caring: responding to nature and the planet"@en ;
  curric:slug "future-fossils-drawing-and-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will look at the theme of fossils as a starting point for this unit. They
  make and abstract a drawing of a fossil using chalk pastels and charcoal. Pupils design
  and make a 3D fossil of the future sculpture using the casting process and design
  principles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit encourages pupils to think critically about the relationship
  between humans and the natural world at a time when environmental issues are increasingly
  urgent and visible. By studying how artists respond to nature and environmental change,
  pupils learn that art can be both imaginative and purposeful - a way to communicate care,
  responsibility, and hope. This unit also gives pupils an opportunity to develop their voice
  as young artists -making choices, expressing opinions, and creating artworks that respond to
  real issues that affect their futures.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2718-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2718-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2718-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2718-4 ;
  curric:id "2718"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.486948Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2721
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Lettering: graphic design"@en ;
  curric:slug "lettering-graphic-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will investigate letterforms and practice calligraphic techniques, looking
  at the work of artists and designers. They will make concrete poems, playing with
  typographic forms to create meaning and communicate ideas. They will design and create
  their own letterform composition."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit has an emphasis on drawing and painting letters precisely, which
  aims to improve pupils' fine motor skills. The ability to draw block lettering with a degree
  of accuracy is a skill that is used repeatedly throughout the key stage. Pupils are
  increasingly confident to make creative choices and select media and techniques that match
  their intentions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2721-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2721-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2721-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2721-4 ;
  curric:id "2721"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.509380Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-2709
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Creature Construction: sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "creature-construction-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will combine readily available scrap items into model animals, learning how
  to construct through assembling materials. They will develop their ability to draw and
  shade 3-dimensions"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops observational studies into sculpture. They will develop
  their ability to select and assemble materials, revisiting themes of upcycling that they
  explored in key stage one.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2709-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2709-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2709-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2709-4 ;
  curric:id "2709"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.553720Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2725
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Abstract art: drawing, printing and textiles"@en ;
  curric:slug "abstract-art-drawing-painting-and-textiles" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will learn how abstract artists convey feelings and emotions through their
  use of colour, line and shape. They will take part in practical abstract exercises,
  including multiple print making with a paper-cut technique, before designing and creating
  an abstract felt panel."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils return to abstract themes explored in previous units.
  This unit is the pupils' most comprehensive study of abstract art. They will learn many of
  the principles and techniques used by artists to convey feeling and emotion before applying
  them to their own composition. This unit introduces new textiles and printing processes,
  materials and techniques.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2725-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2725-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2725-3 ;
  curric:id "2725"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.555607Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-textiles .

oakcurric:unit-2720
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Me in a box: drawing and sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "drawing-and-sculpture-self-identity" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will devise and make a personalised assemblage sculpture that reflects
  aspects of their inner and outer personality. They will compose a poetry self-portrait
  before researching, gathering and collecting items for their assemblage sculpture."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils were introduced to basic assemblage techniques and use of found
  materials in previous units. Here pupils make more sophisticated selections to create art
  that conveys a personal message. Pupils at this stage are able to draw on a range of art,
  craft and design experiences and this project develops their sense of self as artists, makers
  and designers.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2720-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2720-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2720-3 ;
  curric:id "2720"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.565727Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2708
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Monsters: sculpture and digital design"@en ;
  curric:slug "monsters-sculpture-and-digital-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """This design and make unit has links with the creative industries. Pupils will
  identify and study monsters in film and paintings, before realising their own imaginative
  concepts into models and animation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """It is important for pupils to understand that artists influence all of the
  images and ideas they see in film, TV and computer games. Many artists and animators working
  in the film industry started by making simple drawings, models and animations such as these.
  Modern technology means it is very accessible for pupils to do this too.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2708-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2708-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2708-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2708-4 ;
  curric:id "2708"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.613797Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-3738
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sculpture: make a mask"@en ;
  curric:slug "sculpture-make-a-mask" ;
  rdfs:comment """Masks have been created and used by many cultures and peoples through the ages,
  including in contemporary society for film and TV. In this unit, pupils will learn various
  sculpture techniques, design and make a mask."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces new sculpture materials and techniques. Pupils have
  developed sufficient fine motor control to manipulate materials to realise their intentions
  at this stage, and to apply their prior knowledge to this new challenge. In this unit pupils
  will use their knowledge of portraiture and structure of the face in the context of sculpture
  and 3D design.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3738-6 ;
  curric:id "3738"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.698481Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2719
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Hidden worlds: collage and mixed media"@en ;
  curric:slug "hidden-worlds-drawing-and-mixed-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will investigate micro-organisms & create observational drawings in pencil,
  charcoal and watercolour paint, before creating prints & pictures in mixed media collage."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils develop thier understanding of abstract composition, building upon
  thier knowledge from other units. Working in a variety of media, they make independent
  choices and select those that best meet their intentions. Pupils might link these studies
  with their curriculum work in science: studying the cells of plants or animals, pollen, plant
  roots or bone for example.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2719-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2719-2 ;
  curric:id "2719"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.732256Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage .

oakcurric:unit-2713
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Architecture: drawing and 3D design"@en ;
  curric:slug "architecture-drawing-and-3d-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils investigate an architect and learn to draw buildings in an
  architectural style. They may work in groups to respond to an architectural design
  challenge and design and make a solution in two and three dimensions, before making a
  group presentation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning in this unit builds on prior investigations into the built
  environment. Pupils will learn how buildings are designed and how their environment is shaped
  by artists. The unit links to vocational practice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2713-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2713-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2713-3 ;
  curric:id "2713"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.814613Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2730
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "War and conflict in art: textiles"@en ;
  curric:slug "war-and-conflict-in-art-textiles" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit can be linked with pupils' studies in other curriculum areas on World
  Wars. They will draw from observation and investigate how artists have responded to war
  and conflict through textiles, before using their personal ideas of conflict to create an
  appliqué panel."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The unit relates to other curriculum areas and is an ideal way of
  visualising thoughts and feelings pupils may have gathered from their poignant wartime
  studies.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2730-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2730-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2730-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2730-4 ;
  curric:id "2730"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.816546Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-textiles .

oakcurric:unit-2711
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Recycled robots: drawing and sculpture"@en ;
  curric:slug "recycled-robots-drawing-and-sculpture" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils design and make a robot using recycled materials. They will
  investigate robots in film and TV, and create their own recycled robot using construction
  techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have previously explored ways to reclaim and recycle materials.
  They will apply their knowledge and skills to realise more elaborate design ideas in three
  dimensions. Pupils will need to manipulate found materials to their intentions, and refine
  and realise their ideas with increasing purpose and sophistication.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2711-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2711-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2711-3 ;
  curric:id "2711"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.819617Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2714
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Views of a local landmark: ceramics"@en ;
  curric:slug "views-of-a-local-landmark-ceramics" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will learn about composition in landscape, and respond to a local landmark.
  They will use this knowledge to interpret different viewpoints and perspectives in their
  own unique way. They will develop these studies into a low relief ceramic tile, using a
  variety of clay techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Observation is a principal area of the subject which must be revisited in
  order for key skills to progress develop. Pupils will apply their understanding of basic
  elements of composition understand to create 3-dimensional depth sculpturally in low relief.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2714-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2714-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2714-3 ;
  curric:id "2714"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.862639Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2723
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ceramics: cake culture"@en ;
  curric:slug "ceramics-cake-culture" ;
  rdfs:comment """Cake is a central part of many cultures and celebrations, with a rich history and
  symbolic meaning. Pupils will use the subject matter of cakes to develop their drawing and
  painting skills before designing and making a cake of their own invention in clay."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils awareness of their technical ability is increasing at this age.
  This unit encourages them to apply the skills that they have acquired for imaginative
  purposes, and to draw on their own cultural heritage and experiences. It introduces new
  ceramics techniques, extending their skills and knowledge.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2723-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2723-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2723-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2723-4 ;
  curric:id "2723"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.866602Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2716
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dream portraits: drawing and digital design"@en ;
  curric:slug "dream-portraits-drawing-and-digital-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores how dreams have inspired artists, especially the Surrealists.
  Pupils will illustrate a piece of dream text, then learn how to draw and shade a sleeping
  portrait, before transforming it into a digital design."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The Surrealists were a key movement in western art and design who continue
  to have a profound influence on culture to this day. This unit will address key artistic
  skills in drawing and tonal shading, before developing knowledge and understanding of digital
  design and composition.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2716-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2716-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2716-3 ;
  curric:id "2716"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.880556Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-2715
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Local landscape : painting"@en ;
  curric:slug "local-landscape-painting" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will study a local landscape artist and make photographic records of
  natural or park scenes. This could include natural elements within a built environment.
  They will learn some basic landscape painting techniques and apply them to their own
  personal landscape painting."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops awareness of colour, line and pattern and introduces
  important art component knowledge and skills for later development. Pupils will use
  understanding of digital editing to produce original source material.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2715-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2715-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2715-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2715-4 ;
  curric:id "2715"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.035908Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-3831
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Imagined spaces and shared stories"@en ;
  curric:slug "imagined-spaces-and-shared-stories" ;
  rdfs:comment """Made in collaboration with October Gallery, the unit looks at how materials can be
  transformed into imagined and shared stories. Pupils create new worlds and think about how
  art can shape and celebrate real ones. They investigate how public art holds stories of
  pride, memory, and transformation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit supports children to see themselves as both inventors and
  changemakers. It builds imaginative fluency while rooting creative expression in
  collaborative practice and cultural awareness. Each lesson encourages children to reimagine
  their environments: What could a scrap become? What might our shared tower say to the world?
  The sequence nurtures empathy, creative problem-solving, and sculptural fluency. Aligned with
  the national curriculum, it builds foundational skills while fostering reflection, invention,
  and community pride.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3831-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3831-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3831-3 ;
  curric:id "3831"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.124808Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 .

oakcurric:unit-2712
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Perfect Patterns: drawing and design"@en ;
  curric:slug "perfect-patterns-drawing-and-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will create a range of art outcomes based on the theme of patterns. They
  will look at patterns in the natural world and investigate how pattern and decoration
  forms a fundamental part of art making. They will make a pattern motif and use it to
  create their own repeat pattern."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Through pattern making, pupils develop fine motor skills, improve hand eye
  coordination, and increase knowledge and understanding about colour, and shape.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2712-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2712-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2712-3 ;
  curric:id "2712"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.138010Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2731
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Creative careers: critical and contextual"@en ;
  curric:slug "creative-careers-critical-and-contextual" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will learn about different jobs within the creative industries. They will
  investigate and find out what a range of individuals all do in their day to day lives.
  They will carry out research and record their findings in creative visual formats working
  to the theme of 'festival'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """As pupils near the end of Key Stage 2 and prepare for the next phase of
  their educational journey, they should be aware of the important role art, craft and design
  serves in our society and be informed about potential careers within the creative industries.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2731-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2731-2 ;
  curric:id "2731"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.184469Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-textiles ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2710
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Insects: drawing and printmaking"@en ;
  curric:slug "insects-drawing-and-printmaking" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will explore the world of insects up close, recording their observations
  using line drawing techniqes. They will develop these drawings through a number of print
  processes, before creating and realising a design for surface print."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will practice recording from close observation of primary and
  secondary sources, using line drawing techniques developed in earlier units. They will learn
  how to transfer drawings into print media and how to develop a design motif. Their
  explorations of repeat pattern will be developed with more sophisticated compositions in
  later units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2710-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2710-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2710-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2710-4 ;
  curric:id "2710"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.537456Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-print .

